('13004', '1', 'Whatever else you wish to dip'),
('13004', '2', 'Put the chopped or grated cheese into the fondue pot with the wine and heat until boiling on the stove, by which time the cheese should have melted.'),
('13004', '3', 'Turn the pot down to a simmer.'),
('13004', '4', 'Whisk together the cornstarch with the Kirsch in a small bowl, and add to the fondue pot along with the garlic clove.'),
('13004', '5', 'Season with the pepper and nutmeg and move the fondue pot onto a flame at the table.'),
('13004', '6', 'Serve with various vegetables to dip.'),
('13006', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('13006', '2', 'In a small bowl whisk together the lemon juice, salt, pepper and olive oil. Set aside.'),
('13006', '3', 'Put the endive and apples into a large decorative serving bowl. Squeeze the juice of half a lemon into the bowl and toss to coat the endive and apples so they don''t turn brown.'),
('13006', '4', 'Add the cheese and avocado, and then add the cranberries and corn.'),
('13006', '5', 'Pour the dressing over the salad just before serving and toss to coat.'),
('13008', '1', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('13008', '2', 'Place beets on a lightly greased 8-inch square glass baking dish. (If using both red and golden beets, separate on different sides of pan to prevent red from bleeding onto golden.)'),
('13008', '3', 'Pour 2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar and next 4 ingredients over beets. season with salt and pepper. Cover tightly with foil.'),
('13008', '4', 'Bake at 400 for 40 to 45 minutes or until tender. Uncover and let cool to room temperature, reserving beet juice. Peel beets (see tips, below), and slice into 1/4-inch rounds.'),
('13008', '5', 'Separate leaves of endive, and tear radicchio into large pieces. arrange on a large platter or shallow bowl. Layer beets, oranges, fennel, and onion.'),
('13008', '6', 'Whisk mustard and remaining 2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar into reserved beet juice. season with salt and pepper.'),
('13008', '7', 'Serve with salad.'),
('13008', '8', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('13011', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.'),
('13011', '2', 'Place the duck breasts on a sheet pan, skin side up. Sprinkle with salt and roast for about 20 minutes, until medium-rare.'),
('13011', '3', 'Remove from the oven, cover tightly with aluminum foil, and allow to sit for 10 to 15 minutes.'),
('13011', '4', 'Remove and discard the fat and skin on top (unless you''re making cracklings), slice the duck, and then cut the slices crosswise into julienned pieces.'),
('13011', '5', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the shallots, sherry vinegar, orange zest, and 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt.'),
('13011', '6', 'Whisk in the olive oil and set aside.'),
('13011', '7', 'For the salad, trim the bottom half-inch from the endive and cut them diagonally into 1/2-inch slices. Separate the leaves and discard the cores.'),
('13011', '8', 'Place the slices in a large salad bowl.'),
('13011', '9', 'Add the mache leaves, oranges, raspberries, and toasted pecans. Toss with enough dressing to moisten. Gently toss in the warm duck meat and serve immediately.'),
('13014', '1', 'Winter Greens with Olive Vinaigrette and Goat Cheese Croutons'),
('13014', '2', 'Slice the goat cheese into four rounds and place them in a small, shallow bowl in a single layer. Don''t worry if they''re not gorgeous, since you''ll be spreading them on the croutons later anyway.'),
('13014', '3', 'Pour 2 tablespoons of the olive oil over top and sprinkle evenly with the thyme and pepper. Ideally, you should marinate these in the fridge for a few hours, but if you don''t have the time, just set it aside at room temperature while you prepare the rest of the salad.'),
('13014', '4', 'Preheat the oven or a toaster oven to 400F. Rub the baguette slices with the cut sides of the garlic clove, and brush them with the remaining teaspoon olive oil.'),
('13014', '5', 'Bake in a small, shallow baking pan until lightly browned around the edges, about 10 minutes.'),
('13014', '6', 'Let cool slightly. Then spread each crouton with one round of goat cheese. drizzle a bit of the marinade on top. Return to oven for about 5 minutes, until goat cheese is warm.'),
('13014', '7', 'Meanwhile, thoroughly wash the escarole, ,chicory and endive. Tear the escarole and chicory into bite-size pieces. slice the endive crosswise, discarding the root end. Toss together to distribute. When you return the croutons to oven with goat cheese on them, pour some Olive Vinaigrette onto the salad a little at a time and toss, reserving a little dressing to drizzle over the croutons. Divide the salad among four plates, garnish each with a crouton, and drizzle a little dressing over each crouton.'),
('13014', '8', 'Olive Vinaigrette'),
('13014', '9', 'Note: This vinaigrette only gets better as it sits in the fridge for a few days, so you can make it in advance or make extra if you like.'),
('13014', '10', 'Combine the anchovy and garlic on a cutting board. Finely chop them together and then mash to a paste with the side of a chef''s knife.'),
('13014', '11', 'Transfer the paste to a bowl or a small glass jar with a lid.'),
('13014', '12', 'Add the minced shallot, lemon juice and vinegar to the anchovy paste, season with pepper, and let sit for ten minutes.'),
('13014', '13', 'Add the chopped olives, parsley and olive oil. Close the jar and shake to combine, or whisk together thoroughly.'),
('13015', '1', 'Using a glass jar with a tight lid, combine the vinegar, mustard, garlic, salt, and pepper, and shake well to blend.'),
('13015', '2', 'Add the oil and parsley and shake.'),
('13015', '3', 'On 4 plates, arrange the endive leaves like spokes around each plate. Arrange the watercress or spinach in the center. Preheat the broiler, and arrange the sliced apples slightly overlapping in 4 fan shapes, place in broiler pan.'),
('13015', '4', 'Cut the cheese into 4 slices and top each apple fan with slices of cheese. Broil until golden for approximately 5 minutes. Using a spatula, carefully place the apple slices and cheese on top of the endive.'),
('13015', '5', 'Drizzle the dressing over the salads and sprinkle with walnuts.'),
('13016', '1', 'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('13016', '2', 'Add the crab and cook for 13 minutes.'),
('13016', '3', 'Drain and let cool. Lift the carapace and clean the crab of all the butter and lungs inside. Break the crab in half. Separate the legs from the body and crack them open. Extract all the leg meat carefully. try to keep it intact.'),
('13016', '4', 'Next, split the body and pick out all its meat. Go through all the crabmeat after it is picked to remove any stray shell fragments. Set the crabmeat aside in the refrigerator.'),
('13016', '5', 'Remove any tough stems from the watercress. Wash and dry it well.'),
('13016', '6', 'Peel and finely dice the shallots.'),
('13016', '7', 'Carefully peel the zest from the lemons with a sharp vegetable peeler, being sure to take only the yellow peel and none of bitter white pith. If you do end up with some pith, pare it away with a sharp paring knife.'),
('13016', '8', 'Cut the pieces of zest crosswise into a julienne and combine with the shallots in a small bowl. Season generously with salt and freshly ground pepper.'),
('13016', '9', 'Squeeze the lemons and add about 5 tablespoons of the juice to the bowl with the shallots and lemon zest.'),
('13016', '10', 'Add the Champagne vinegar, mix well, and let sit for at least  hour to macerate.'),
('13016', '11', 'Whisk in the olive oil. taste for salt, pepper, and acid and adjust as needed.'),
('13016', '12', 'When you are ready to serve the salad, remove any blemished outer leaves from the endives.'),
('13016', '13', 'Cut them in half lengthwise and remove the cores, then cut lengthwise into strips.'),
('13016', '14', 'Put them in a serving bowl with the watercress, crab, and vinaigrette and toss well. Arrange on a platter or individual plates and serve immediately.'),
