('13018', '1', 'Heat oven to 425F.'),
('13018', '2', 'Place beets in roasting pan or on baking sheet. drizzle with oil.'),
('13018', '3', 'Bake 45 min. to 1 hour or until tender.'),
('13018', '4', 'Remove from oven. cool 20 min.'),
('13018', '5', 'Remove skins.  Slice beets. cut slices into strips.'),
('13018', '6', 'Meanwhile, bring vinegar and thyme to boil in small saucepan.  Simmer on low heat 10 min. or until reduced to about 3 Tbsp. liquid, stirring occasionally.  Strain and cool.'),
('13018', '7', 'Arrange endive, oranges, shallots and beets on serving platter.'),
('13018', '8', 'Drizzle with balsamic reduction. top with cheese and pepper.'),
('13019', '1', 'Plunge squid into a large saucepan of boiling water, then remove pan from heat and let stand, stirring once or twice, 1 1/2 minutes.'),
('13019', '2', 'Drain squid in a colander and cool.'),
('13019', '3', 'Cut squid bodies crosswise into thin slices and halve tentacles crosswise.'),
('13019', '4', 'Scrub mussels and rinse well, then cook in a 5- to 6-quart heavy pot over moderately high heat, covered, until shells are opened, 4 to 6 minutes, checking frequently after 4 minutes and transferring mussels as opened to a bowl. (Discard any unopened mussels after 6 minutes.) Cool mussels, then remove from shells.'),
('13019', '5', 'Whisk together vinegar, citrus juices, oil, garlic, salt, and pepper in a bowl and add squid, mussels, fennel, onion, and parsley, tossing to combine.'),
('13019', '6', 'Serve salad on endive leaves.'),
('13021', '1', 'In a mini food processor, puree the quince paste with the water and balsamic vinegar.'),
('13021', '2', 'Add 1/4 cup of the olive oil and process until emulsified.'),
('13021', '3', 'Pour the quince dressing into a small bowl and season with salt and pepper.'),
('13021', '4', 'In a small saucepan, cook the garlic in the remaining 2 tablespoons of oil over moderate heat until the garlic is golden brown, about 4 minutes. Discard the garlic.'),
('13021', '5', 'Put the endives, escarole, frise and radicchio in a large bowl.'),
('13021', '6', 'Pour the hot garlic oil on top and toss.'),
('13021', '7', 'Add the quince vinaigrette and the blue cheese to the salad, toss again and serve.'),
('13022', '1', 'Whisk together shallot, honey, orange juice, vinegar, salt, and white pepper in a bowl, then add olive oil in a stream, whisking until combined.'),
('13022', '2', 'Toss endives, onion, fennel, celery root, apple, and mizuna with 1/2 cup dressing in a large bowl. Season with salt and white pepper.'),
('13022', '3', 'Serve salad topped with cheese and drizzled with truffle oil.'),
('13022', '4', '*Available at specialty foods shops and many supermarkets.'),
('13022', '5', '**Available at specialty foods shops and Dean & DeLuca (800-221-7714).'),
('13024', '1', 'To make garlic oil, combine the olive oil and garlic in a small saucepan over medium heat. When the garlic starts to sizzle, remove from the heat and let sit for half an hour. Discard the garlic cloves and set the oil aside.'),
('13024', '2', 'Cut the endives in half lengthwise, remove the cores, and slice into strips  inch wide. In a medium bowl, toss the endives, frise, cucumber, and fennel with the garlic oil, lemon juice, and salt and pepper to taste.'),
('13024', '3', 'ON THE PLATE: Divide the salad among 4 plates and top with shaved Parmigiano-Reggiano.'),
