('13027', '1', 'Bring verjus, Port, and sugar to a boil in a 1-quart heavy saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then boil until syrupy and reduced to about 1/3 cup, 8 to 12 minutes.'),
('13029', '1', 'Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat).'),
('13029', '2', 'Mix 1 1/2 cups water, coarse salt, and sugar in 11 x 7 x 2-inch glass baking dish. stir until salt and sugar dissolve.'),
('13029', '3', 'Add pork chops. let brine 20 minutes, turning occasionally.'),
('13029', '4', 'Cut Treviso and endive lengthwise into quarters, keeping some core attached to each piece.'),
('13029', '5', 'Place on baking sheet. brush with some oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Boil vinegar in small skillet until reduced to 1/4 cup, about 5 minutes.'),
('13029', '6', 'Whisk in butter. Season glaze with salt and pepper.'),
('13029', '7', 'Remove pork from brine. pat dry.'),
('13029', '8', 'Brush with oil. sprinkle with pepper. Grill pork, Treviso, and endive until vegetables are softened and thermometer inserted horizontally into center of chops registers 150F, 2 to 3 minutes per side for vegetablesand 7 to 8 minutes per side for chops.'),
('13029', '9', 'Transfer pork and vegetables to plates.'),
('13029', '10', 'Drizzle glaze over. sprinkle with parsley.'),
('13032', '1', 'In a large bowl, beat the eggs. Stir in the mascarpone until blended.'),
('13032', '2', 'Add 1/2 cup of the drained kimchi, two-thirds of the minced garlic, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and the ginger. Fold in the crabmeat and 1/2 cup of the panko or plain dry bread crumbs. Pat the crabmeat mixture into 6 burgers, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until the crab burgers are chilled and firm, about 30 minutes.'),
('13032', '3', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix the mayonnaise with the lime juice, sambal oelek, mustard, lime zest and the remaining minced garlic. Season with salt and pepper. In a large bowl, toss the endives with the carrot, the remaining 1 cup of kimchi and 2 tablespoons of the pickling juice.'),
('13032', '4', 'Spread the remaining panko on a plate and coat the burgers. In a very large nonstick skillet, heat 1/4 inch of oil.'),
('13032', '5', 'Add the burgers and cook over moderately high heat, turning once, until browned, 7 minutes.'),
('13032', '6', 'Drain on paper towels.'),
('13032', '7', 'Spread the mayonnaise on the toasted brioche. Set the crab burgers on the brioche toast and top with the kimchi slaw. Close the crab burger sandwiches and serve.'),
('13035', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('13035', '2', 'Whisk the vinegar, mustard, oregano, salt and pepper in a large bowl to blend. Gradually whisk in the oil.'),
('13035', '3', 'Add the crabmeat and toss gently to coat.'),
('13035', '4', 'Arrange the endive spears on a platter. Spoon the crabmeat atop the endive spears. Sprinkle with chives and serve.'),
('13039', '1', 'Heat oil in large nonstickskillet over medium heat.'),
('13039', '2', 'Add onion andstir 1 minute to coat with oil.'),
('13039', '3', 'Add vinegarand sugar and stir until onion begins tosoften slightly, about 3 minutes.'),
('13039', '4', 'Transferonion to baking sheet or platter. spread insingle layer. Sprinkle with salt. Cover andchill at least 8 hours or overnight (onion willturn pink). DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 daysahead. Keep chilled.'),
('13041', '1', 'In a stockpot large enough to hold all ingredients, heat oil over medium-high heat and add pancetta and onions. Cook until onion starts to brown, then add farro and stir to mix well. Bring 2 cups of water to a boil and stir into the farro mixture. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low. cover and cook very slowly, adding more boiling water from time to time as the grain begins to absorb the water.'),
('13041', '2', 'When the kernels start to get tender, add the celery, escarole, zucchini, and chicory. Stir in the marjoram and tomato sauce, and adjust seasoning with salt and pepper. Continue cooking until farro is very tender and serve immediately with grated cheese.'),
('13041', '3', 'In a 3-quart saucepan, heat the olive oil over medium heat.'),
('13041', '4', 'Add the onion and garlic and cook until soft and light golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('13041', '5', 'Add the thyme and carrot and cook until the carrot is quite soft, about 5 minutes more.'),
('13041', '6', 'Add the tomatoes and their juice and bring to a boil, stirring often. Lower the heat and simmer until as thick as hot cereal, about 30 minutes. Season with salt, to taste.'),
('13041', '7', 'This sauce holds 1 week in the refrigerator or up to 6 months in the freezer.'),
('13044', '1', 'Heat olive oil and butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat.'),
('13044', '2', 'Add the onions and sugar, and cook until the onions are golden brown and caramelized.'),
('13044', '3', 'Add the garlic and cook for 2 minutes.'),
('13044', '4', 'While the onions are cooking, place the potatoes in a medium saucepan filled with cold salted water. Bring to a boil and cook until the potatoes are just cooked through.'),
('13044', '5', 'Drain the potatoes and set aside.'),
('13044', '6', 'Add the clam broth to the onions and bring to a simmer.'),
('13044', '7', 'Add the oysters and the potatoes and simmer just until the oysters have cooked through, about 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('13044', '8', 'Whisk in the creme fraiche and season with salt and pepper.'),
('13044', '9', 'Remove from the heat and stir in the tarragon.'),
('13044', '10', 'Serve with Winter Green Salad and Green Apple Vinaigrette.'),
('13044', '11', 'Combine greens, celery, apples, and cheese in a large bowl.'),
('13044', '12', 'Whisk together both vinegars and the shallot. Slowly whisk in the oil, and season with salt and pepper. Toss the salad ingredients with some of the vinaigrette.'),
('13045', '1', 'Combine all ingredients except endive leaves and sour cream.'),
('13045', '2', 'Spoon onto endive leaves.'),
('13045', '3', 'Top with sour cream.'),
('13046', '1', 'To make the beef roast, preheat the oven to 475 degrees F.'),
('13046', '2', 'Place the beef roast on a clean work surface and rub with the olive oil and chopped rosemary.'),
('13046', '3', 'Place into the preheated oven and cook for 15 minutes and then turn the heat down to 350 degrees F. Cook for about 15 minutes per pound for rare meat, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.'),
('13046', '4', 'Remove from the oven and let rest, covered, for about 15 minutes before slicing.'),
('13046', '5', 'To make the Yorkshire Pudding, preheat the oven to 450 degrees F.'),
('13046', '6', 'Mix the milk, eggs, and salt, and add pepper, beating all well together. I use my freestanding mixer but a hand-held electric mixer, rotary, or balloon whisk would do.'),
('13046', '7', 'Let these ingredient stand for 15 minutes and then whisk in the flour. Meanwhile, add the drippings a large heat-proof pan and put it in the oven to heat for about 10 minutes. Into this intensely hot pan you should pour in the batter and cook for 20 minutes, or until well puffed and golden. Bring it, triumphant, to the table.'),
('13046', '8', 'To make the grilled eggplant, place the garlic-oil into a shallow dish and set aside. On a clean work surface, slice the eggplant into long, thin slices and then place into the garlic-oil, turning to coat.'),
('13046', '9', 'Preheat a griddle or stove top grill pan and then place each eggplant slice onto the grill. Cook about 2 to 3 minutes and then turn, and cook 2 to 3 minutes more.'),
('13046', '10', 'Remove the grilled slices to a platter and drizzle with more of the garlic-oil.'),
('13046', '11', 'Garnish with coarse salt, cracked black pepper, lemon juice and snipped chives.'),
('13046', '12', 'To make the pea, mint and avocado salad, first make the dressing: put the oil, vinegar, and sugar into a large bowl and then put in a decent handful of the chopped mint. Stir well so all is amalgamated. Cook the peas for 2 minutes or so in salted boiling water, just so that they''re ready, but not soft. Taste after 2 minutes and keep tasting.'),
('13046', '13', 'Drain the peas in a colander, put them straightaway into the bowl of dressing, and let steep for 1 hour or up to a day.'),
('13046', '14', 'Just before serving, stir in the mixed greens, the endive, and the avocado. You may need to drizzle a bit more oil after tossing.'),
('13046', '15', 'Serve this on a big plate. Sprinkle with some more of the chopped mint.'),
('13048', '1', 'To make the marinade, whisk the oil, mint, lime juice, ginger, chiles, and garlic. Season with salt.'),
('13048', '2', 'Add the shrimp and mix. Refrigerate for at least 15 minutes and up to 1 hour.'),
('13048', '3', 'To serve, divide the endive among 4 salad plates. Top with the shrimp and garnish with the watercress and lime wedges.'),
('13048', '4', 'Serve immediately.'),
